Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Peel @Yukon Gold potatoes{12%ounce}, then cut into ½-inch cubes. Place in a #medium pot{} with a big pinch of @salt{} and enough water to cover by 1 inch. Bring to a boil and cook until easily pierced by a #knife{}, ~{12-15%minutes}. Drain and return to #pot{}.

Use a #mallet{} or heavy pan to crush @tricolor peppercorns{1/4%teaspoon} in their bag until coarsely ground. Finely chop @parsley{1/4%ounce}. Peel, halve, and chop @shallot{1}. Toss @green beans{6%ounce}, a drizzle of @vegetable oil{}, and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{} on a #baking sheet{}. Roast in oven until tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Heat a drizzle of vegetable oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Pat @New York strip steak{12%ounce} dry with a #paper towel{} and season all over with salt and pepper. Add to pan and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-6%minutes} per side. Remove from pan and set aside to rest.

> Loosely cover steak with aluminum foil to keep it warm.

Reduce heat under pan to medium low and add a drizzle of oil. Add shallot and cook until softened, ~{1-2%minutes}, tossing. Stir in ¼ tsp crushed peppercorns (use more or less to taste), @beef demi-glace{1}, and @water{1/2%cup}. Bring to a boil, then lower heat and simmer until reduced, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from heat. Add @butter{1%tablespoon} and half the sour cream and stir until butter is melted. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add remaining @sour cream{4%tablespoon} and @truffle oil{1/2%teaspoon} to pot with drained potatoes (we sent extra oil—use more or less to taste). Mash with a #potato masher{} or #fork{} until smooth. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

> Add a splash of milk to make potatoes extra creamy.

Thinly slice steak against the grain. Toss green beans with @almonds{1%ounce}. Divide mashed potatoes, green beans, and steak between plates. Drizzle sauce over steak and potatoes. Garnish with parsley.